NEW module C:\Users\Arda\workspaces\@cogitave\tabos\crates\tb-hal\src\blocks.rs, header `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` (identical discipline to ipc.rs/mem.rs). Contents:

  use alloc::rc::Rc; use alloc::vec::Vec; use core::cell::{Cell, RefCell};
  /// One bi-temporal blackboard record version (the RECORD plane / CAS store).
  pub struct Rec { pub off: u64, pub val: u64, pub version: u64, pub supersedes: u64 }
  /// A pinned, quota'd shared segment. Held behind Rc<Block> so EVERY member's
  /// HandleTable holds an Rc-clone of the SAME core (the ipc::Channel pattern).
  pub struct Block {
      frames: Vec<u64>,              // FRAME plane: ordered M6 PAs == the shared bytes
      n_pages: usize,                // == frames.len(); bytes = n_pages*4096
      members: RefCell<Vec<(u64,u64,bool)>>, // (root_pa, base_va, writable) live mappings — for refcount/hard-detach
      seq: Cell<u64>,                // seqlock/version word for the whole block
      records: RefCell<Vec<Rec>>,    // RECORD plane: kernel-mediated CAS/versioned slots (append-only, bi-temporal)
  }
  impl Block {
      /// Allocate n_pages M6 frames, ZERO each (no tenant-byte leak — seL4/Zircon
      /// zero-on-handout), record PAs. fail-closed -> None on OOM, freeing partial.
      pub fn create(n_pages: usize) -> Option<Rc<Block>> { /* loop frame_alloc(); on None free prior + return None */ }
      pub fn frames(&self) -> &[u64];          // accessor for the map facade
      pub fn n_pages(&self) -> usize;
      pub fn record_member(&self, root_pa: u64, base_va: u64, writable: bool); // push to members (safe RefCell)
      /// RECORD-plane CAS: if latest version of slot `off` == expected, append a
      /// superseding Rec (keep BOTH bi-temporally) bump seq, return Ok(new_ver);
      /// else Err. Atomic w.r.t preemption (single-core, interrupts masked).
      pub fn cas_write(&self, off: u64, val: u64, expected: u64) -> Option<u64>;
      pub fn read_latest(&self, off: u64) -> Option<u64>;
  }

WIRING in caps.rs:
- ObjKind (caps.rs:200): APPEND `Block` AFTER `Generic` (last variant) so existing #[repr(u32)] discriminants — returned raw by M_OBJECT_INSPECT — stay stable. Do NOT reuse `Skill` (it is tagged "(M15)" but is the T4 procedural-memory kind, a documented mislabel).
- Object struct (caps.rs:223): add field `block: Option<Rc<crate::blocks::Block>>` paralleling `chan`. ALL FOUR existing Object{} literals (mint:480, mint_memory_home:490, mint_record:504, mint_channel_endpoint:524) must gain `block: None` or it will not compile.
- HandleTable::mint_block (the mint_channel_endpoint twin, ~caps.rs:520): `pub(crate) fn mint_block(&mut self, rights: Rights, blk: Rc<Block>) -> Option<Handle> { self.alloc(rights, Rc::new(Object{ kind: ObjKind::Block, mem:None, scalar:0, chan:None, block:Some(blk) })) }`.
- HandleTable::block_of (new, the map facade's resolver — mirrors live()+payload fetch): `pub(crate) fn block_of(&self, h: Handle) -> Result<(Rights, Rc<Block>), SysStatus> { let i=self.live(h)?; let o=self.slots[i].object.clone().ok_or(SysStatus::Stale)?; match &o.block { Some(b)=>Ok((self.slots[i].rights, b.clone())), None=>Err(SysStatus::BadCap) } }`.

REACHED AS A CAPABILITY: an agent holds a Block Handle in its per-principal HandleTable; the frames are owned by Rc<Block> and live while any handle references the object (Zircon refcount, same as Channel/MemoryHome). Sharing = give each member's table an Rc-clone Block handle (kernel facade agent_block_create, the agent_channel_connect precedent at lib.rs:1421). The single source of bytes is the Rc<Block>; mapping it into N roots makes the bytes appear in N address spaces.

design.selftest:
SLOT: kernel/src/main.rs immediately AFTER the M14 marker (line 1741 `serial_write_str("M14: ipc OK\n")`) and BEFORE the final tb_hal::halt() (1743). REUSE agent_c and agent_d (the M14 members) as session members A and B — no new task slots, exactly as M13/M14 reused them. Timer already disarmed (single-core, interrupts masked). Mirror the m14_fail closure (main.rs:1561). Define `fn m15_fail(why)->!` (prints "M15: FAIL <why>" then halt). Let ok=Ok as u32, den=Denied, badcap=BadCap, badmethod=BadMethod; rd=Rights::READ.bits(), wr=Rights::WRITE.bits(), BLOCK_VA=0x0000_0280_0000_0000.

STEP 1 CREATE: let (hb_c, hb_d) = agent_block_create(agent_c, agent_d, 1) else m15_fail("block create failed");  // 1 frame, both Rc-cloning ONE blocks::Block::create(1). hb_c=READ|WRITE|TRANSFER|DUP, hb_d=READ|WRITE.

STEP 2 MAP into BOTH roots:
  let (s,_) = agent_block_map(agent_c, hb_c, true, BLOCK_VA).unwrap(); if s!=ok { m15_fail("map into C not Ok") }
  let (s,_) = agent_block_map(agent_d, hb_d, true, BLOCK_VA).unwrap(); if s!=ok { m15_fail("map into D not Ok") }
  // both BLOCK_VA now translate to the SAME frame PA in two different roots.

STEP 3 TRUE SHARING (the north-star — distinguishes from M14's COPY; rides KERNEL-side I/O because leaves are kernel-only):
  tb_hal::address_space_switch_root(tb_hal::agent_root_pa(agent_c));
  let _ = tb_hal::addr_store_load(BLOCK_VA, 0xB10C);          // A writes the shared frame under its OWN root
  tb_hal::address_space_switch_root(tb_hal::agent_root_pa(agent_d));
  let seen = tb_hal::addr_load(BLOCK_VA);                      // B reads the SAME frame under its OWN root
  tb_hal::address_space_switch_default();
  if seen != 0xB10C { m15_fail("B did not read the bytes A wrote (no true sharing)") }
  serial_write_str("blocks: A wrote, B read the SAME bytes (true sharing)\n");

STEP 4 RO REJECTION (cap-layer, portable — see risk re CR0.WP, NOT a hardware fault):
  let (s, hb_d_ro_raw) = agent_block_dispatch(agent_d, M_HANDLE_NARROW, hb_d, rd as u64, 0,0).unwrap(); if s!=ok { m15_fail("narrow hb_d drop WRITE failed") }
  let hb_d_ro = Handle::from_raw(hb_d_ro_raw);
  let (s,_) = agent_block_dispatch(agent_d, M_BLOCK_WRITE, hb_d_ro, 0, 0xDEAD).unwrap(); if s!=den { m15_fail("RO handle M_BLOCK_WRITE was not Denied") }
  // and the map of a RO handle requesting write downgrades to RO (permission = min):
  let (s, _) = agent_block_map(agent_d, hb_d_ro, /*want_writable=*/true, BLOCK_VA+0x1000).unwrap(); if s!=ok { m15_fail("RO map not Ok") }
  // assert the recorded member is writable==false (min(request,rights) dropped WRITE) — checked via a blocks test accessor OR by re-reading members.
  serial_write_str("blocks: RO handle write Denied + map downgraded to RO\n");

STEP 5 RECORD-PLANE update-once-visible-everywhere (the kernel-mediated blackboard):
  let (s,_) = agent_block_dispatch(agent_c, M_BLOCK_WRITE, hb_c, /*off*/0, /*val*/0x1234).unwrap(); if s!=ok { m15_fail("C record write not Ok") }
  let (s,v) = agent_block_dispatch(agent_d, M_BLOCK_READ, hb_d, 0, 0).unwrap(); if s!=ok || v!=0x1234 { m15_fail("D did not read C's record (blackboard not shared)") }
  serial_write_str("blocks: C wrote record, D read it (update-once-visible-everywhere)\n");

STEP 6 DENIED / NON-BLOCK / BADMETHOD paths:
  let gen = agent_mint_generic(agent_c, Rights::READ.union(Rights::WRITE)).unwrap();
  let (s,_) = agent_block_dispatch(agent_c, M_BLOCK_READ, gen, 0,0).unwrap(); if s!=badcap { m15_fail("M_BLOCK_READ on a non-block was not BadCap") }
  let (s,_) = agent_block_map(agent_c, gen, false, BLOCK_VA).unwrap(); if s!=badcap { m15_fail("M_BLOCK_MAP on a non-block was not BadCap") }
  let no_read = Handle::from_raw(agent_block_dispatch(agent_c, M_HANDLE_NARROW, hb_c, 0/*empty mask*/, 0).unwrap().1);
  let (s,_) = agent_block_map(agent_c, no_read, false, BLOCK_VA).unwrap(); if s!=den { m15_fail("map with a READ-less block handle was not Denied") }
  let (s,_) = agent_block_dispatch(agent_c, 32, hb_c, 0,0).unwrap(); if s!=badmethod { m15_fail("unknown block method 32 was not BadMethod") }

STEP 7 MARKER: tb_hal::serial_write_str("M15: blocks OK\n");  // the DoD marker. All M2..M14 markers still print (no regression). (Single-agent path = the same code with members={agent_c}; |members|=1, no special case.)
